      "wall_description": "During the winter of 1888, Monet visited Antibes in southern France. Under the Mediterranean sun his colors became lighter and brighter, and his paint surfaces more thickly impastoed. \"What I bring back from here,\" he wrote, \"will be sweetness itself, white, pink, and blue, all enveloped in a magical air.\" The brilliant colors -- warm pinks, corals, cool greens, and blues -- embody the sun-soaked atmosphere of the Mediterranean coast.",
