      "fun_fact": "This brass head represents a Benin ruler wearing accouterments that speak to his divine power, such as the elaborate headdress and the beaded collar around his neck. Also notice the scarification, or intentional skin marking, above his eyes. The practice of scarification is common among some African peoples as it denotes the ethnicity or clan ties of the individual who bears them.",
